# File Structure Convention

Canonical layout for everything under `src/`. Read before adding any file. The route-island skill ([`agent-os/skills/route-island/SKILL.md`](../skills/route-island/SKILL.md)) implements these rules step-by-step; this is the contract.

## The pages rule in five lines

1. **`src/pages/` mirrors the URL tree 1:1.** `/login` → `pages/login/`; `/organization/org_8fK2x/dashboard` → `pages/organization/$organizationId/dashboard/`. Children nest **directly** (no `sub-pages/` bucket); dynamic segments are `$param` folders with full-word names. One exception: `/` is a pure resolver route (redirect only, no island).
2. **Every page folder maintains the same 4 files** — `<page>.route.tsx`, `<page>.manifest.ts`, `<Page>Page.tsx` (or `<Page>Layout.tsx`), `<PAGE>.OVERVIEW.md` — plus 2 registrations: `src/app/routes/routeTree.tsx` and `docs/reference/routes-and-ui.md`. `$param` folders derive their prefix mechanically (strip `$`, kebab-case).
3. **Page shells live in `shared/layouts/`** — `AuthLayout` via the pathless `auth-shell` route; `AppShell` via the `pages/organization/$organizationId/` layout island (the org guard boundary). No grouping directories under `pages/`.
4. **Promotion ladder:** one page → inside that page; a page + its OWN nested children → that page's `shared/` (family-shared, e.g. `pages/organization/$organizationId/shared/`); pages from different families or any `src/shared` component → root `src/shared/` (`shared/api/auth-api.ts`, `shared/tenancy/`, …).
5. **Settings is a global hash modal, not a route space** — `#settings/<scope>/<section>` (see "Settings hash modal" below). Full routing/tenancy spec: `docs/reference/routing-and-tenancy.md`.

## Top-Level Layout

```
tests/                                  At project root: e2e/, load/, factories/, utils/
src/
├── app/                                Application shell: route tree, guards, providers, error boundaries
├── core/                               Framework-agnostic services
├── pages/                              Page-first feature directories (each = a frontend route)
├── shared/                             Cross-page reusables: components, forms, hooks, layouts, store
├── lib/                                Pure utilities (no side effects)
├── App.tsx
├── main.tsx
└── index.css
```

**`src/core/`** is the irreducible platform kernel — only framework-agnostic, app-state-free services: `http/`, `rbac/`, `config/`, `data-provider/`, `resources/`, `types/`, `version/`. **Anything app-shell-y, React-Provider-y, or app-state-dependent lives outside `core/`:**
- App-shell bootstrap (Sentry init, web-vitals, PostHog setup) → **`src/app/`** (`app/analytics/`, `app/observability/`)
- Runtime infrastructure used by every layer (auth token + service, errors handling) → **`src/shared/`** (`shared/auth/`, `shared/errors/`)
- Zustand client state → **`src/shared/store/<X>Store/`** (folder-per-unit) — all 5 stores including `useAuthStore` and `useOrganizationStore`
- Cross-page API helpers → **`src/shared/api/`** (`auth-*`, `organization-*`)
- Organization/tenancy runtime (URL-driven context, membership, `/` resolver, my-organizations) → **`src/shared/tenancy/`**

## Naming — three categories

### 1. Role files — page-prefixed, lowercase-dotted

One per page. The prefix makes them globally unique → AI agents, grep, and IDE quick-open all resolve without ambiguity.

| File | Required? | Purpose |
|------|-----------|---------|
| `<page>.route.tsx` | ✓ | Lazy boundary (`Component`, `loader`, `ErrorBoundary`) |
| `<page>.manifest.ts` | ✓ | Manifest: `path`, `testId`, `permission`, `kind`, `children` |
| `<page>.contracts.ts` | optional | Zod schemas + inferred TS types |
| `<page>.api.ts` | optional | Fetcher functions for this page |
| `<page>.search.ts` | optional | URL search-param schema (TanStack Router `validateSearch`) |
| `<page>.fixtures.ts` | optional | Mock generators (marked `REPLACE_WITH_API`) |
| `<page>.constants.ts` | optional | Page-scoped constants |
| `<page>.resource.ts` | resource pages only | Resource manifest (endpoint, schema, permissions) |

### 2. Entry doc — `<PAGE>.OVERVIEW.md` (UPPER_SNAKE name · dotted role)

| File | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `<PAGE>.OVERVIEW.md` | AI/human entry doc — first file an agent reads on this island. Name = UPPERCASE directory name with `-` → `_`; the dot separates name from role, mirroring the `<page>.route.tsx` grammar (`pages/forgot-password/` → `FORGOT_PASSWORD.OVERVIEW.md`). Every overview filename is globally unique (grep/quick-open/agent file-matching never collide) while staying visibly a doc, like `README.md`. Applies outside `pages/` too: `shared/api/API.OVERVIEW.md`, `shared/auth/AUTH.OVERVIEW.md`, `app/guards/GUARDS.OVERVIEW.md`. |

### 3. UI files — PascalCase

| File | When |
|------|------|
| `<Page>Page.tsx` | Top-level UI; manifest `kind: 'leaf'` |
| `<Page>Layout.tsx` | Top-level UI; manifest `kind: 'layout'` (mounts `<Outlet />`) |
| Sub-units in `components/`, `forms/`, `hooks/`, `dialogs/`, `store/` | See "Folder-per-unit" below |

## Folder-per-unit (components, forms, hooks, dialogs, store)

Every component / form / hook / dialog / store lives in its own folder with three files:

```
<Name>/
├── <Name>.tsx              source (or .ts for hooks/store)
├── <Name>.test.tsx         test (or .ts)
└── index.ts                export { <Name> } from './<Name>.tsx';
```

Apply to:
- `components/<Name>/`
- `forms/<Name>Form/`
- `hooks/use<Name>/`
- `dialogs/<Name>Dialog/`
- `store/use<X>Store/`

**Sub-unit names are not page-prefixed** — the path already provides context:
- ✓ `pages/dashboard/components/ActivityFeed/`
- ✗ `pages/dashboard/components/DashboardActivityFeed/`

**Exception — shadcn primitives stay flat.** `src/shared/components/ui/` keeps the shadcn convention (`button.tsx`, `card.tsx`, etc.) — no folder-per-unit.

**Exception — cohesive flat groups.** A multi-file component group that only makes sense as a set keeps flat files inside its parent folder: `shared/components/data-table/` and the `SettingsModal` panel groups (`account/`, `organization/`). Tests colocate beside the group's logic files. Everything else follows folder-per-unit.

## Page Naming (directory)

| Pattern | Use for | Example |
|---------|---------|---------|
| **Plural noun** | Collection / list view | `pages/organizations/` → `/organizations` |
| **Singular noun** | Single resource (current context) | `pages/organization/` → `/organization` (user's current org) |
| **kebab-case verb-noun** | Action / workflow | `pages/create-organization/` → `/create-organization` |
| **kebab-case noun** | Multi-word concept | `pages/accept-invite/` → `/accept-invite` |

Page directory names are **lowercase kebab-case**. Child route folders follow the same rules and nest directly (`organization/$organizationId/api-keys/`); dynamic segments are `$param` folders with full-word param names (`$organizationId/`, `$patientId/` — never `$orgId`).

**Sanctioned exception:** `pages/organization/` is singular yet serves the picker (a collection view) at `/organization` — it doubles as the `$organizationId/` parent, so the URL spec (`routing-and-tenancy.md` §2) wins over the plural-for-collections naming row.

## Two page shapes — custom and resource

### Custom page

For pages that aren't a backend resource (dashboard, login, callback, onboarding, accept-invite):

```
src/pages/<page>/                          ← folder = URL segment
│
│══ MANDATORY — every page, validator-enforced ════════════════════════════
├── <PAGE>.OVERVIEW.md                     entry doc: purpose, files, test ids
├── <page>.route.tsx                       lazy boundary — Component (+ loader: requirePermission)
├── <page>.manifest.ts                     manifest — path, testId, permission, kind, children
├── <Page>Page.tsx | <Page>Layout.tsx      top-level UI (Layout + <Outlet/> when kind:'layout')
│
│══ OPTIONAL — the page's OWN data layer ══════════════════════════════════
├── <page>.contracts.ts                    Zod schemas + types for THIS page's API shapes
├── <page>.api.ts                          fetchers → shared apiClient   (PRIVATE to this page,
│                                          even from its children — sharing goes via shared/)
├── <page>.fixtures.ts                     mock data (REPLACE_WITH_API)
├── <page>.search.ts                       URL search-param schema (validateSearch)
├── <page>.constants.ts                    page-scoped constants
├── <page>.resource.ts                     resource manifest (resource pages only)
│
│══ OPTIONAL — units (each: <X>.tsx + <X>.test.tsx + index.ts) ════════════
├── components/<Widget>/                   page-only widgets
├── forms/<Name>Form/                      page-only forms
├── hooks/use<X>/                          page-only Query hooks (wrap <page>.api.ts)
├── dialogs/<Name>Dialog/                  URL-driven dialogs (resource pages)
├── store/use<X>Store/                     RARE page-local Zustand
├── __tests__/integration/                 this page's cross-component flows
│
│══ OPTIONAL — FAMILY-SHARED (kind:'layout' only) ═════════════════════════
├── shared/                                used by THIS page + its children — never other families
│   ├── components/<X>/  hooks/use<X>/     same unit shapes as root shared
│   └── <name>-contracts.ts · <name>-api.ts   family-scoped plain modules
│
│══ OPTIONAL — children (kind:'layout' only; disk mirrors URL) ════════════
└── <child>/  ·  $param/                   full recursive copy of this exact anatomy
                                           (`shared` & unit names are reserved — can't be routes)
```

### Resource page

For pages that map to a backend resource (organizations, members, roles, invitations, api-keys, billing):

```
src/pages/<resource>/
├── <RESOURCE>.OVERVIEW.md
├── <resource>.route.tsx                   parent route — renders the list
├── <resource>.manifest.ts                     kind: 'layout', children: ['create', '$id', '$id-edit']
├── <resource>.resource.ts                 resource manifest (endpoint, schema, permissions)
├── <resource>.contracts.ts                Zod — shared across all CRUD views
├── <resource>.api.ts                      optional; most resources use shared CRUD hooks
├── <Resource>ListPage.tsx                 top-level UI — the list
├── components/<Name>/{...}                list widgets (Table, Filters, EmptyState)
├── forms/<Name>Form/{...}                 reusable forms consumed by dialogs
├── dialogs/<Name>Dialog/{...}             URL-driven action dialogs
├── hooks/use<Name>/{...}                  resource-specific hooks (most use shared CRUD)
├── create/                                → /<resource>/create   (renders null; list opens dialog)
└── $<resource>Id/                         → /<resource>/[id]     (show — full-name $param folder)
    └── edit/                              → /<resource>/[id]/edit (renders null; list opens dialog)
```

Resource pages use `<Resource>ListPage.tsx` (PascalCase, page-prefixed) as the top-level UI. The list page mounts the action dialogs and reads URL to open them.

## CRUD UX convention — URL-driven dialogs

For resource pages, the standard mapping:

| Action | URL | Renders | Why URL? |
|--------|-----|---------|----------|
| **List** | `/<resource>` | Page | Destination; must be shareable |
| **Create** | `/<resource>/create` | Dialog over list | Refresh-safe, deep-linkable |
| **Show** | `/<resource>/[id]` | Page or dialog over list | Shareable detail link |
| **Edit** | `/<resource>/[id]/edit` | Dialog over list | Refresh-safe, deep-linkable; `[id]` loads the row |
| **Delete** | *(no URL)* | Inline `AlertDialog` confirm | Transient one-click destructive action |
| **Quick toggles** | *(no URL)* | Inline button / dropdown | Transient |

On disk, `[id]` is a full-name `$param` folder — `$memberId`, `$invoiceId` (never `$id`); its role files use the strip-`$` kebab prefix (`member-id.route.tsx`).

**Implementation pattern.** Parent `<Resource>ListPage.tsx` reads `useRouterState({ select: s => s.location.pathname })`, computes which dialog (if any) the URL implies, and renders it open. The list stays mounted behind the dialog backdrop.

**Forward compatibility — promoting dialog → full page.** When a Create/Edit dialog outgrows the modal (multi-step wizard, >15 fields, file uploads, shareable drafts):
1. URL stays the same (`/<resource>/create` or `/<resource>/[id]/edit`)
2. Replace the dialog mount in the list page with the sub-page's `route.tsx` rendering a full `<X>Page.tsx`
3. No URL break, no bookmark break

## Index redirects

When a layout has children, its index route (`/`) **redirects to the default child** via `beforeLoad`:

```ts
const indexRoute = createRoute({
  getParentRoute: () => parentRoute,
  path: '/',
  beforeLoad: () => { throw redirect({ to: '/parent/default-child' }); },
  component: () => null,
});
```

Established cases:
- `/` → resolver route (last-used organization's dashboard, else `/organization`, else `/onboarding`)
- Future resource layouts with multiple children pick a default child

## Nested routes — direct children (`<segment>/`, `$param/`)

When a page is `kind: 'layout'`, child routes nest **directly** as `<segment>/` — the pages tree mirrors the URL tree 1:1; there is no `sub-pages/` bucket. Dynamic segments are `$param` folders with full-word param names (`$organizationId/`, `$patientId/`).

**`$param` naming rule (validator-enforced):** role files in a `$param` folder derive their prefix mechanically — strip the `$`, kebab-case the rest: `$organizationId/` → `organization-id.route.tsx`, `organization-id.manifest.ts`, `ORGANIZATION_ID.OVERVIEW.md`. Only the UI file stays human-named (`OrganizationLayout.tsx`, `PatientDetailPage.tsx`).

**Reserved segment names (validator-enforced):** `components`, `hooks`, `forms`, `dialogs`, `store`, `shared`, `__tests__` can never be route folders; `sub-pages` is retired. A `shared/` directory inside a layout page is the **family-shared** home (see Promotion ladder).

```
pages/organization/                       → /organization (picker)
├── organization.route.tsx
├── organization.manifest.ts                  kind: 'layout', children: ['$organizationId']
├── OrganizationPickerPage.tsx
└── $organizationId/                      → /organization/$organizationId (org guard boundary)
    ├── organization-id.route.tsx
    ├── organization-id.manifest.ts           kind: 'layout', children: ['dashboard', 'suspended']
    ├── OrganizationLayout.tsx
    ├── dashboard/                        full island shape, recursively
    └── suspended/
```

## Settings hash modal (and the `/` resolver)

Settings is **not a route space**. The global `SettingsModal` (`shared/components/SettingsModal/`) is mounted once on the root route and driven by the URL hash — `#settings/<scope>/<section>` with scopes `account` | `organization` — so it overlays ANY page (including deep organization URLs) without re-running route matching or unmounting the page behind it. Deep links reproduce page + modal, refresh keeps the section, back/Esc closes, and invalid hashes fall back to `#settings/account/profile`.

Route guards never see hashes: auth, organization-context, and permission gating live inside the modal (`settings-permissions.ts`, reusing `core/rbac` — never forked). Open/section state lives in the URL hash — never in `useUIStore` (the store is only for transient chrome: `sidebarOpen`, `commandPaletteOpen`). Hash changes are invisible to pageview analytics, so the modal emits an explicit PostHog event. Escape hatch: a section that becomes a heavy admin surface (members, billing, …) is promoted to a real page under `pages/organization/$organizationId/`, keeping a hash → path redirect shim.

`/` is the other folder-less URL: a pure resolver route (last-used organization's dashboard, else the `/organization` picker, else `/onboarding`) registered inline in `routeTree.tsx`.

## Dialog vs full page — decision tree

When a sub-path exists under a page:

1. **Does it need a URL?**
   - YES → either URL-driven dialog (sub-page renders null, parent shows dialog) or full page (sub-page renders Page UI)
   - NO → local state (`useState` in parent's component)
2. **Page or dialog?**
   - **Page** when: complex, table-heavy, multi-step, mobile real estate matters, deep-link to detail context
   - **Dialog** when: form fits in modal, action stays in list context, transient
3. **Rule.** Everything between two `<page>.route.tsx` files belongs to the parent route's component.

## Promotion ladder (where code lives, by who uses it)

Everything starts **colocated** with its page. It climbs exactly one rung per force — never higher:

```
used by…
  ONE page                                → inside that page (components/, hooks/, <page>.api.ts, …)
  the page + its OWN nested children      → pages/<parent>/shared/        (family-shared)
  pages from DIFFERENT families,
  or any src/shared component             → src/shared/                   (root shared)
  every layer / platform-level            → src/core/ or src/lib/
```

**Family-shared (`pages/<parent>/shared/`)** — for layout pages whose children share code:
- Same unit shapes as root shared: `shared/components/<X>/`, `shared/hooks/use<X>/`, plus plain family modules (`<name>-contracts.ts`, `<name>-api.ts`).
- Importable by the parent island and its descendants ONLY — never by sibling families.
- Example: a chart widget used by `$organizationId/dashboard/` AND `$organizationId/reports/` → `pages/organization/$organizationId/shared/components/<X>/` (NOT `src/shared/`).
- Note: the auth screens (`login/`, `register/`, …) are top-level **siblings** (no parent island — the `auth-shell` is pathless), so their shared code correctly lives in root `shared/api/auth-*` — different families.

**Never promote when:**
- Only one page uses it (even if it looks "generic")
- It contains page-specific business logic

Promotion: move to the lowest rung that covers all consumers, update imports project-wide, delete the original — never copy.

## Shared Layer

```
src/shared/
├── components/
│   ├── ui/                                 shadcn primitives — FLAT (button.tsx, card.tsx, ...)
│   ├── <Name>/{...}                        cross-page components — folder-per-unit
│   └── ...
├── forms/<Name>/{...}                      cross-page forms
├── hooks/
│   ├── use<X>/                             cross-page custom hooks
│   ├── useList/, useOne/                   standard CRUD hooks (Refine-style)
│   ├── useCreate/, useUpdate/, useDelete/
├── layouts/<Name>/{...}                    RootLayout, AppShell, AuthLayout
└── store/                                  GLOBAL Zustand stores
    ├── useThemeStore/{...}
    ├── useUIStore/{...}
    └── useOnboardingStore/{...}
```

## Core Layer

The irreducible, app-state-free platform kernel — one subfolder per domain:

```
src/core/
├── config/                                 env schema, constants
├── data-provider/                          CRUD abstraction (REST adapter, mock adapter)
├── http/                                   apiClient (fetch + axios), interceptors, queryClient, mock helper
├── rbac/                                   policies + guards (requireAuth, requirePermission)
├── resources/                              resource registry (central manifest)
├── types/                                  branded public-id types, permission codes
└── version/                                new-deployment detection
```

Auth runtime lives in `shared/auth/`, organization/tenancy runtime in `shared/tenancy/`,
errors in `shared/errors/`, and analytics/observability bootstrap in `app/` — see
"Top-Level Layout" above for why each sits outside the kernel.

## State Management

| Scope | Library | Location |
|-------|---------|----------|
| Server state | TanStack Query | `pages/<page>/hooks/use<X>/` or `shared/hooks/use{List,One,Create,Update,Delete}/` |
| Global client state | Zustand | `src/shared/store/use<X>Store/` (incl. `useOrganizationStore` — current tenant) |
| Page-local client state | Zustand | `src/pages/<page>/store/use<X>Store/` *(rare)* |
| Component-local | `useState` / `useReducer` | Inline; extract reducer to `<Component>.reducer.ts` when complex |
| Form state | react-hook-form + Zod | Inside the form component |
| URL state | TanStack Router | `<page>.search.ts` (validateSearch schema) |

**All Zustand stores live in `src/shared/store/<X>Store/`** (folder-per-unit) — `useAuthStore`, `useOrganizationStore`, `useThemeStore`, `useUIStore`, `useOnboardingStore`. There is no `core/<feature>/store.ts` pattern.

Cross-page API helpers (functions reused by both `pages/` and `shared/components/`) live in **`src/shared/api/`** (e.g., `shared/api/organization-api.ts`); organization/tenancy runtime lives in **`src/shared/tenancy/`** (e.g., `shared/tenancy/my-organizations.ts`).

Auth infrastructure (token storage, refresh timer, idle timeout, login/logout service, mocks) lives in **`src/shared/auth/`** — not in core, because the HTTP client, error handler, shared components, and pages all need it.

**Rules:**
1. **Server state never goes in Zustand.** TanStack Query owns it.
2. **Page-local stores are an escape hatch** — try `useState` → `useReducer` → URL search params → shared store FIRST.
3. **Reducers live next to the component** that uses them. No `reducers/` directory.

## Tests

| Type | Location |
|------|----------|
| Unit (component, hook, form, util, store) | Colocated `<Name>.test.{ts,tsx}` next to source |
| Page integration (cross-component flow in this island) | `pages/<page>/__tests__/integration/` |
| E2E (full browser, cross-page) | `tests/e2e/` at project root (Playwright) |
| Load | `tests/load/` (k6) |

**No test file required for:**
- `<page>.route.tsx` (thin wrapper)
- `<page>.manifest.ts` (declarative manifest)
- `<page>.contracts.ts` (Zod — type-checked at compile, exercised where used)
- `<PAGE>.OVERVIEW.md`, `index.ts` (barrel re-exports)

## Import Rules

- Always use `@/` alias for imports from `src/`
- Always include `.ts`/`.tsx` extensions: `import { Button } from '@/shared/components/Button/index.ts'`
- Type-only imports: `import type { Org } from './<resource>.contracts.ts'`

**Dependency direction (one-way, with one documented exception):**

```
shared/components/ui ─── may import other ui primitives + lib
lib                  ─── may import from lib, core/types only
core                 ─── may import from lib, core/types (+ runtime trio, see below)
shared               ─── may import from core, lib, types
pages                ─── may import from shared, core, lib, types
app                  ─── may import from everything
```

**Runtime-trio exception (the only one):** the core kernel (`core/http`, `core/rbac`) may
import `shared/auth/`, `shared/errors/`, `useAuthStore`, and `useOrganizationStore`. Token
handling, error reporting, and permission checks are runtime services the kernel provides,
but that infrastructure is app-state- and SDK-dependent (Zustand, `@sentry/react`) so it
lives in `shared` (see Top-Level Layout). Core must never import any other `shared`
module. Enforced precisely by `no-restricted-imports` in `eslint.config.mjs`.

**Family-shared imports:** a page may import its ANCESTOR island's `shared/` (`pages/<parent>/shared/...`) — that folder exists to be shared down the subtree. A parent's role files (`<parent>.api.ts`, …) stay private to the parent; the explicit sharing surface is `shared/`.

**Never:**
- Page imports another page (`pages/A/` ↛ `pages/B/`) — including another family's `shared/`
- Shared imports from pages
- Core imports from pages, app, or any shared module outside the runtime trio
- UI primitives (`shared/components/ui/`) import anything internal except other ui primitives and `lib`

